@startuml sequence-v2
title TO-BE: P2P Transfer — Decision Hub Architecture

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline

actor Client
participant "API Gateway\n:8000" as GW #LightBlue
participant "Payment Service\n:8001" as PS #LightYellow
participant "Decision Hub\n:8002" as DH #LightCoral
database "decision_rules\ndecision_audit" as DB #LightGray
participant "Ledger Mock\n:8003" as LM #LightGreen

== Happy Path: APPROVE ==

Client -> GW: POST /api/p2p/transfer\nIdempotency-Key: key-001\n{amount: 50000, country: "KZ", device_trust: "HIGH", ...}

GW -> GW: Generate X-Correlation-Id: corr-xyz\n(if not in request)

GW -> PS: POST /p2p/transfer\nX-Correlation-Id: corr-xyz\nIdempotency-Key: key-001

PS -> PS: Check idempotency table\n→ key-001 not found, continue

PS -> PS: Create transfer\nstatus = NEW\ntransfer_id = uuid-111

PS -> DH: POST /decision/evaluate\n{\n  decision_type: "P2P_TRANSFER",\n  context: {amount, country, device_trust, ...},\n  correlation_id: "corr-xyz"\n}

DH -> DB: SELECT * FROM decision_rules\nWHERE active=true\nORDER BY priority ASC

DB --> DH: [LIMIT_DAILY(p=1), AML_102(p=2), FRAUD_017(p=3)]

note over DH
  Rule Engine evaluates in priority order:
  LIMIT_DAILY: 0 + 50000 > 10000000? NO → skip
  AML_102: "KZ" in blocklist? NO → skip
  FRAUD_017: trust=HIGH? NO → skip

  Result: APPROVE, risk_score=null
end note

DH -> DB: INSERT INTO decision_audit\n(decision_id, transfer_context,\n rules_checked, final_decision=APPROVE)

DB --> DH: OK

DH --> PS: {\n  decision_id: "dec-abc",\n  allowed: true,\n  decision: "APPROVE",\n  reasons: [],\n  rules_evaluated: 3,\n  rules_matched: 0\n}

PS -> PS: Update transfer\nstatus: NEW → DECIDED\ndecision_id = dec-abc

PS -> LM: POST /ledger/posting\n{transfer_id: uuid-111, amount: 50000}

LM -> LM: Create posting\nstatus = POSTED

LM --> PS: {posting_id: "post-999", status: "POSTED"}

PS -> PS: Update transfer\nstatus: DECIDED → POSTED

PS -> PS: Save idempotency snapshot\nkey-001 → cached response

PS --> GW: 200 {\n  transfer_id: "uuid-111",\n  status: "POSTED",\n  decision: {decision_id, allowed: true, reasons: []},\n  posting: {posting_id, status: "POSTED"}\n}

GW --> Client: 200 + X-Correlation-Id: corr-xyz\n+ X-RateLimit-Remaining: 99

== Scenario: REJECT (AML) ==

Client -> GW: POST /api/p2p/transfer\nIdempotency-Key: key-002\n{amount: 50000, country: "IR", ...}

GW -> PS: POST /p2p/transfer\nX-Correlation-Id: corr-uvw

PS -> DH: POST /decision/evaluate\n{context: {country: "IR", ...}}

note over DH
  LIMIT_DAILY: NO
  AML_102: "IR" in ["IR","KP","CU","SY"]? YES → REJECT
  → Stop evaluation (first REJECT wins)
end note

DH -> DB: INSERT decision_audit\n(final_decision=REJECT,\n rules_matched=[AML_102])

DH --> PS: {\n  allowed: false,\n  decision: "REJECT",\n  reasons: [{\n    rule_id: "AML_102",\n    reason_code: "AML_COUNTRY_BLOCKED",\n    owner: "compliance"\n  }],\n  risk_score: 0.95\n}

PS -> PS: Update transfer\nstatus: NEW → REJECTED

PS --> GW: 200 {\n  status: "REJECTED",\n  decision: {reasons: [{rule_id, owner, reason_code}]}\n}

GW --> Client: 200 {status: "REJECTED",\n  decision: {reasons: [AML_102]}}

note over Client
  NOW you can answer every question:

  "Which rule blocked it?" → AML_102
  "Who owns it?" → compliance team
  "What version?" → 2.1
  "Show audit log?" → GET /decision/audit/dec-abc
  "What else was checked?" → rules_checked in audit
end note

== Idempotency: Retry ==

Client -> GW: POST /api/p2p/transfer\nIdempotency-Key: key-001\n(same key as before)

GW -> PS: POST /p2p/transfer\nIdempotency-Key: key-001

PS -> PS: Check idempotency table\n→ key-001 FOUND → return cached response

PS --> GW: 200 {same response as first call, idempotent: true}

GW --> Client: 200 (identical to first call)\nNo duplicate transfer created\nNo duplicate posting made

@enduml
